<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-04-08T01:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-04-08T01:35:00-05:00" n="383" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.00/1857: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-08T10:00:00+03:25">April 8,
                                    1942—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 10:36 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>99. Reference my No. 98, April 7. Prime Minister called me early this
                            morning to tell me he is not satisfied with Majlis’ decision refusing to
                            expel Japanese and that he is calling another secret session tomorrow in
                            a final endeavor to obtain such action. Meanwhile British Minister has
                            telegraphed London reporting this decision and requesting
                            instructions.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>